Bonnie “Bo” RubergAssistant ProfessorDepartment of Film and Media StudiesSchool of HumanitiesUniversity of California, Irvine











 
















Bonnie “Bo” Ruberg is an assistant professor of digital games and interactive media in the Department of Film and Media Studies at UC Irvine. Their research explores gender and sexuality in digital media and digital cultures. They are the author of Video Games Have Always Been Queer (2019, New York University Press), the co-editor of Queer Game Studies (2017, University of Minnesota Press), and the co-organizer and co-founder of the annual Queerness and Games Conference.





































